          "subtitle": "Asking about people",
          "pattern": "누구예요? → 우리 N이에요/예요.",
          "meaning": "Who is that person?",
          "description": "Use 누구예요? to ask who someone is. When answering about family, use 우리 (my/our) before the family word. It shows the person belongs to your family!",
          "rule_boxes": [
            {
              "color": "blue",
              "label": "❓ 누구예요? = Who is it?",
              "examples": [
                "누구예요? → 우리 엄마예요! (It's my mom!)",
                "누구예요? → 우리 아빠예요! (It's my dad!)"
              ]
            },
            {
              "color": "green",
              "label": "🏠 우리 = My (family/things)",
              "examples": [
                "우리 엄마 = my mom",
                "우리 집 = my house",
                "우리 학교 = my school",
                "💡 Korean says '우리' (our) even for one person's family!"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "examples": [
            { "korean": "누구예요? — 우리 할머니예요.", "english": "Who is it? — It's my grandmother.", "highlight": "우리 할머니" },
            { "korean": "누구예요? — 우리 아빠예요.", "english": "Who is it? — It's my dad.", "highlight": "우리 아빠" },
